label.phrase: what's different in this procedure is that you will also have a cup or more of trimmed duck fat if you'd like to render it it's great for cooking cut it into pieces and cook it slowly in a skillet until all the fat has liquefied and the bits of skin have become crisp drain and eat the crispy bits and refrigerate the fat it will keep for weeks
